Our brains are wired to make split second decisions.

Here is a real life example: I moved to Chicago two months ago from Nashville. I was constantly being told how dangerous it is and how I would not be able to go anywhere or do anything safely. The people telling me this were not from Chicago and most had not even visited but the media gave them the impression that it was a lawless and danger-filled land.

Take a look at the beauty industry. Over the past few years there have been countless content creators displaying elaborate packages they have received from PR. These companies send a huge display box filled with whatever new product they are releasing. These packages sometimes even include music or interactive items. They know that by sending these packages, content creators will review the products on their platform, whether they are good or bad. This is exposure to them. This impression will remain in the viewers minds, even if the product ends up getting a bad review.
